15:
Huh?! It's the beginning of a new
year! Why're you being a sourpuss
already?
35:
Cacow! Battle Royale: All Star
Smash, loading complete!
40: No escape from crossing fate! GO!
44: So you'll resist until the very end.
48: Don't say I didn't warn you!
53: Time to finish this! Bubble Trapper!
75: There they are. Right on time...
84:
Allow me to explain! Battle Royale:
All Star Smash, or BRASS for short, is
a competition held between the
twelve states in our world!
89:
Consider it diplomacy through song
and dance battles. Idol warfare to
prevent idle warfare (for the third
year in a row)!
94:
This is Torietta! And I'm Gaiger, her
Cosmic Beast!
97:
Together, we're Retrygerthe
Cosmic Idol group from Tigerton!
101:
Actually, I'm a police officer. Not an
idol.
111:
Hold on... The emblem on your
badge... Is that the Cosmic Idol
Police Department?!
115:
Yep. I'm a Cosmic investigator from
the CIPD.
119:
...Why does it always get more and
more complicated with you people?
124: Are you friends of these idols?
128:
I guess you can call us that. What
kind of trouble did they get
themselves into this time?
133:
We didn't do nothing! This is an
unlawful arrest!
137:
I followed a trail of Cosmic Power
and found the idols of Littleton and
Oxton working together...
140:
This is beyond suspicious! Are you
two colluding together to rig the
BRASS? Or is this something more
sinister?!
145:
You've got it totally wrong! I know
my rights! I want a lawyer!
149:
Yeah, yeah. You can whine all you
want once we get you into a cell.
152:
Dispatch, this is Torietta. Dispatch,
do you read?
155:
...H-huh? Why can't I connect to
them?
159:
Afraid you're not gonna be able to,
no matter how many times you try.
163:
Yeah! Since we're in a different world
and all!
170:
...Yeah, right. Your lies won't work on
me, criminal
176:
No. Despite what's at steak, we're
telling the truth.
179:
Yeah, we're stuck here, looking for a
way to get back to our world.
186:
You've gotta be kidding me... After I
finally got a new start in life...
192:
...Forgive me if I'm wrong, but your
face looks familiar.
194:
Were you once the legendary junior
idol Alestra?
199:
N-no, you've got it all wrong! I'm not
Alestra... I'm no idol!
212:
Uh-oh, she's reverting to her baby
state!
220:
I want my papa and mama!
Waaahh!
224:
She always gets like this when she
gets super stressed! You, over there!
228:
You need to pretend to be her
mama!
246:
Aha... Hahaha... Why did this have to
happen to me...
250:
I'm truly sorry you had to see such a
shameful side of myself...
255:
More like you turned into an entirely
different person, sheesh.
260:
...Hard Rock Magic. Chateaubrilliand
Duo. I'm also very sorry for the
misunderstanding.
263:
I shouldn't have jumped to
conclusions.
267:
Eh, it's fine. You figured it out in the
end!
271:
We all make mis-steaks. So what will
you do from now on?
279:
I don't have the right to ask for
anything after what I just did... But
could I stay here while I look for a
way home?
284:
Of course you can. We welcome
you, Torietta. Gaiger.
288:
Th-thank you so much! As a Cosmic
investigator of the CIPD...
291: I'll do my bwest to pwotect this town!
295:
...Er, I mean, I'll do my best to protect
this town!
